<item>
            <title>[SPARK-6440] ipv6 URI for HttpServer</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-6440</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In &lt;tt&gt;org.apache.spark.HttpServer&lt;/tt&gt; uri is generated as &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;spark:&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;//&quot;&lt;/span&gt; + localHostname + &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;:&quot;&lt;/span&gt; + masterPort&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;, where &lt;tt&gt;localHostname&lt;/tt&gt; is &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt; org.apache.spark.util.Utils.localHostName() = customHostname.getOrElse(localIpAddressHostname)&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;. If the host has an ipv6 address then it would be interpolated into invalid URI:  &lt;tt&gt;spark://fe80:0:0:0:200:f8ff:fe21:67cf:42&lt;/tt&gt; instead of &lt;tt&gt;spark://&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;fe80:0:0:0:200:f8ff:fe21:67cf&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;:42&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The solution is to separate uri and hostname entities.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;java 7 hotspot, spark 1.3.0, ipv6 only cluster&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
